---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="northroot" description="Portable evidence for operational and agentic work.">
  <div class="system-landing">
    <section class="system-hero">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Northroot trust kernel</p>
        <h1>Portable evidence for verifiable work.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Northroot is a trust kernel for append-only records, receipts, and
          offline verification across operational and agentic work. Runtime
          systems can build around it without becoming the source of proof.
        </p>
      </div>
      <aside class="status-panel" aria-label="System status">
        <div class="status-item">
          <span class="status-label">Core</span>
          <span class="status-value">append-only records, receipts, portable journals</span>
        </div>
        <div class="status-item">
          <span class="status-label">Checks</span>
          <span class="status-value">offline verification with explicit outcomes</span>
        </div>
        <div class="status-item">
          <span class="status-label">Boundary</span>
          <span class="status-value">kernel first; runtime and console remain separate</span>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="panel-grid" aria-label="Operational overview">
      <div class="section-panel">
        <p class="section-kicker">Capabilities</p>
        <h2>Core operations</h2>
        <div class="capability-table">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Primitive</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Canonical JSON</td><td>Stable bytes for the same semantic value.</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Records</td><td>Append-oriented evidence for what happened.</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Receipts</td><td>Claims bound to local evidence hashes.</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Journals</td><td>Optional framed replay for offline audit.</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Verification</td><td>Checks that do not require a live service.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-panel">
        <p class="section-kicker">Start here</p>
        <h2>Read the current system</h2>
        <p><a href="/product/portable-evidence/">Portable Evidence</a> defines the current proof shape.</p>
        <p><a href="/product/">Product</a> describes the kernel scope and current non-goals.</p>
        <p><a href="/systems/">Systems</a> explains publishing boundaries and source authority.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="architecture-panel">
      <p class="section-kicker">Architecture</p>
      <h2>One evidence shape across runtimes</h2>
      <p class="summary">Different systems can produce records and receipts that remain inspectable outside the system that produced them.</p>
      <div class="architecture-flow" aria-label="Northroot evidence flow">
        <div class="architecture-node"><strong>Records</strong><span>Structured evidence from external systems.</span></div>
        <div class="architecture-node"><strong>Canonicalize</strong><span>Deterministic bytes and hygiene rules.</span></div>
        <div class="architecture-node"><strong>Receipt</strong><span>Claim bound to evidence hashes.</span></div>
        <div class="architecture-node"><strong>Verify</strong><span>Offline check with no live service dependency.</span></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="panel-grid" aria-label="Reading links">
      <div class="section-panel">
        <p class="section-kicker">Examples</p>
        <h2>First portable bundle</h2>
        <p>Start with the GitHub repo inspection example to see a read-only agentic work item recorded as files, hashes, events, and a receipt.</p>
        <p><a href="/examples/github-repo-inspection/">Open example</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="section-panel">
        <p class="section-kicker">Publishing</p>
        <h2>Drafts require review</h2>
        <p><span class="system-status">draft PR gated</span></p>
        <p>Generated drafts carry source references and remain unpublished until reviewed and merged.</p>
        <p><a href="/systems/publishing-boundary/">Review the boundary</a></p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
